observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Sanggunian Bayan:

Observe the prohibition against expenses for reception and entertainment;

Utilize the concerned Officials’ representation allowance for the cost of meals during regular meetings and En Banc sessions which is the intended purpose of such;

Discontinue charging expenses for meals and snacks served during En Banc sessions/meetings to LGU funds; and

Exercise prudence in its provision for catering/meal services for projects/activities, evaluating which instances truly require such services and allocate excess funds to projects beneficial to the public.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Require the Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count of the Local Government Unit’s (LGU’s) PPE annually and reconcile the same with the recorded PPE in the books;

Instruct the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit in a prescribed format a complete and accurate report of Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) for the current year to the Municipal Accountant and the Commission on Audit (COA) before January 31 of the succeeding year;

In coordination with the Municipal Engineering’s Office, require the Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count and assessment of all public infrastructure assets of the LGU and reconcile with the records in the books; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to recognize depreciation expense for all PPEs annually.

We recommended that the LDRRMO:

Evaluate the unutilized balances of the current year’s five per cent LDRRMF, continuing LDRRMF, and the unexpended LDRRMF transferred to the Trust Fund (TF) books;

Anticipate and promptly address issues and concerns affecting the efficient and effective implementation of LDRRM PPAs to avoid delays or non-implementation;

Maximize LDRRMF utilization focusing on PPAs requiring the highest priority in terms of urgency and/or impact on the four thematic areas of Disaster Risk Reduction and Management and consider the needs of the time, such as the 2019 Corona Virus Disease (COVID-19) emergency; and

Ensure efficient and effective implementation of all programmed and reprogrammed projects during the budget year to optimize the fund’s utilization and warrant that goals and objectives of reducing disaster risk and enhancing disaster preparedness and response capabilities be achieved.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to:
Monitor the status of transferred funds to identify unutilized balances of completed PPAs and comply with COA Circular No. 94-013 on the return of the unexpended balances on a timely manner;
Coordinate with the BTr on how to return the unexpended balances with unidentified or closed SA;
Ensure the accuracy of reported Due to NGAs accounts by ensuring these accounts exist as of year-end; and
Facilitate the immediate return of the two BUB accounts and DILG Local Access Roads.

We recommended that the LDRRMO:
Evaluate the unutilized balances of the current year’s five per cent LDRRMF, continuing LDRRMF, and the unexpended LDRRMF transferred to the TF books;
Anticipate and promptly address issues and concerns affecting the efficient and effective implementation of LDRRM PPAs to avoid delays or non-implementation;
Maximize LDRRMF utilization focusing on PPAs requiring the highest priority in terms of urgency and/or impact on the four thematic areas of Disaster Risk Reduction and Management and consider the needs of the time, such as the COVID-19 and earthquakes; and
Ensure efficient and effective implementation of all programmed and reprogrammed projects during the budget year to optimize the fund’s utilization and warrant that goals and objectives of reducing disaster risk and enhancing disaster preparedness and response capabilities be achieved.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Moving forward, require the Human Resource Management Officer (HRMO) to furnish the COA with copies of Contracts and its supporting documents within five working days after execution thereof in accordance with COA Circular No. 2009-001;
Direct the HRMO to indicate in the contracts of JO workers the duties and responsibilities expected to be performed by them;
Instruct the HRMO, to formulate local policy, in accordance with existing rules and regulations, on standardization of rate given to JO workers for uniform application all throughout the LGU; and
Require the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that the person receiving the salaries is the actual person it is due to, otherwise, request for authorization duly signed by that person.

